Default keyboard shortcut: CTRL-Z
Default tab trigger: (none)
Screenshot: http://cl.ly/1j3G2n0h0Y0U1r0Y453T

Installation: 
==========
1. open Textmate  
2. CTRL-ALT-CMD-B  
3. drag the z-index^2.tmCommand file into the list

4. open a CSS file with z-indexes used  
5. press CTRL-Z

Note:
==========
PHP script and tmCommand are identical in code. You may test the command by running the php file from TextMate by CMD-Shift-R (if you got the PHP bundle).

See also:
==========
CSS Navigator: http://valka.info/projects/css-navigator/
My other TextMate stuff: http://valka.info/projects/css-navigator/plus/